Topic: Average (Easy + Scoring 🔥)
1️⃣ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

Average means:
👉 Equal distribution of total value

📌 Formula:
Average = Total Sum / Number of items

2️⃣ Important Concepts
🔹 Basic Formula

Average = Sum ÷ Number

🔹 Sum Formula

Sum = Average × Number

🔹 Change in Average

If one value is replaced:

👉 Change in total = Difference in value
👉 New average = New sum ÷ Number

3️⃣ Short Tricks (Very Important)
If all values are same → Average = same value
Total = Average × Number
Use deviation method for faster solving
🧠 Example

Average of 5 numbers = 10
👉 Total = 10 × 5 = 50

